\date{2025-02-19}
\title{Goals}

\import{stt-macros}

\p{
We set out in the tradition of the Univalent Foundations Program \citek{HoTT} to
develop informal and formal mathematics alongside each other and to use Agda and type
theory as internal languages for categories of interest, with a particular focus on
the simplicial type theory originally introduced by Riehl–Shulman \citek{RS17}.
}


\ul{
  \li{Develop the base theory of HoTT in the style of the \citek{HoTT} book, as
      a common ground on top of which we can explore synthetic theories. In
      doing so, we will make as much use of Agda's features as necessary in
      order to maximalise the ergonomics of the library. i.e.  type classes,
      metaprogramming, records, notations, modality etc. We will also use a
      small handful of rewriting rules to e.g. to make eliminators of higher
      inductive types compute.}

  \li{Develop a robust theory of modalities.
    \ul{
      \li{Defining 'internal' modalities after Rijke–Shulman–Spitters \citek{RSS20}.
          This will be a crucial organisational tool within the library, allowing us
          a single interface through which we can for instance define the
          subuniverses of [#{n}-types](stt-006P), [#{\infty}-groupoids](stt-00L7) and
          [#{\infty}-categories](stt-00PH), and [indiscrete types](stt-00J2).}
      \li{Develop the theory around the inbuilt idempotent comonadic modality in
          Agda: #{\flat}, establishing the adjunction #{\flat \dashv \sharp} which
          was explored for example by Shulman \citek{Shu17a}.}
    }
  }

\li{Focus on developing synthetic category theory:
  \ul{
  \li{We would like to work inside the classifying #{\infty}-topos of the theory
      of bounded distributive totally ordered lattices, or in other words
      simplicial spaces. To do so we will axiomatise the interval type as the
      universal bounded distributive lattice and explore axioms that can
      internally reflect the structure of our intended model.}

  \li{Formalise the Yoneda-image of the simplex category internally. Including
      defining [#{n}-simplices](stt-00E1), [horns](Synthetic.Horns),
      [boundaries](Synthetic.Boundaries), and the morphisms between them. In
      particular trying to create a pleasant interface to them — comparative to
      the ergonomics of the shape layer in the type theory with shapes of
      Riehl–Shulman \citek{RS17}, as implemented in the Rzk proof assistant
      \citek{rzk}.}

  \li{Formalise #{\infty}-category theory}
  }
}
}
